connected planar obstacles, O1, O2, ¬∑ ¬∑ ¬∑ , ON , a system of representative points, denoted Œ∂l ‚àà Int(Ol), ‚àÄl = 1, ¬∑ ¬∑ ¬∑ , N ,

is a selection of one point in the interior of each obstacle. The

exact location of the representative points is not of particular

signiÔ¨Åcance as long as each lies inside the respective obstacle

interiors.

Note that in general it is possible that two (or more) of

the obstacles might not be mutually disjoint. That is, Oi and Oj can be parts of a same connected obstacle, but

each of these parts need to be connected. This amounts

