Lemma 1 (H-signature as homology class invariant [2]):
Two trajectories œÑ1 and œÑ2 connecting the same points in the plane punctured by obstacles are homologous if and only if H(œÑ1) = H(œÑ2)
Remark: The above lemma gives a way of computing homology invariant in R2 ‚àí O. Note that from the deÔ¨Ånition of H-signature and using the residue theorem from complex analysis, it is easy to see that when œÑ is a closed loop, H(œÑ ) is a vector of the form [a1, a2, ¬∑ ¬∑ ¬∑ , aN ]T 2œÄi, where al ‚àà Z. Moreover, according to the terminology of [2], we call a trajectory non-looping (which is an embedded curve) if the imaginary part of each element of its H-signature is between ‚àí2œÄi and 2œÄi.
