3) CheckNearbyGroupsForRedistribution: If a group has

been assigned homology classes more than the number of robots available in that group (i.e., |Hg| > |g|), then it
is checked if there is another nearby group, g , such that c|Hg | < |g |, Pgt ‚àí Pgt < R (c > 1, R > 0 are parameters). If so, a re-shufÔ¨Çing of the groups is performed
(with dome robots from g being transferred to g) and the
new group arrangement is returned to Gpl+1. Since the

